message.entry: This feature is not available on this platform.\n
Old tic/toc CPU speed was {0} cycles/sec.\n
Overhead of Tic/Toc command is {0} sec.\n
Resolution of Tic/Toc clock is {0} sec.\n
Second argument must be a character vector
Third argument must be a double

Choose second argument from: 
 ''resolution_tictoc'' - Resolution of Tic/Toc clock in sec (double)
 ''overhead_tictoc'' - Overhead of Tic/Toc command in sec (double)
 ''getcpuspeed_tictoc'' - Stored CPU cycles/sec (double) [Used by tic/toc]
 ''cpuspeed'' - Current CPU cycles/sec (double) [Simple MathWorks]
 ''unixtimeofday'' - Current time of day (uint64) [gettimeofday call]
 units: usec since 01-Jan-1970 (UTC)
 ''clocks_per_sec'' - clock() speed in cycles/sec [CLOCKS_PER_SEC]
 ''posixrtperftime'' - Posix real time in nsec (uint64) [clock_gettime call]
 ''posixrtperfspeed'' - Posix real time clock speed (double) [clock_getres call]
 units: cycles/sec
Choose second and third arguments from: 
 ''cpuspeed'', double num - Current CPU cycles/sec (double) [MathWorks - num iterations]
 uint64 arg2, uint64 arg3 - uint64 difference = arg2 - arg3 (uint64)
